markets.title: Will Trump visit areas affected by the LA wildfires?
markets.rules_primary: If Donald J. Trump has visited a part of the Los Angeles metropolitan area directly damaged by the January 2025 Los Angeles area wildfires before March 1, 2025  in order to inspect the damage, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: A visit includes Donald J. Trump’s deliberate physical presence in the area, including on foot, inside a vehicle, or in a helicopter. A visit to comfort people impacted by the damage, to survey the damage, to plan rebuilding efforts, or another similar purpose, will be considered a visit “to inspect the damage”. Conversely, if Donald J. Trump flies over an affected area en route to another destination and is not reported to have journeyed to the affected area  to inspect the damage, that event is not encompassed in the Payout Criterion.
markets.early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the event occurs.
